[BEGIN] The Associated Press reports Syria's Foreign Minister has said his country has accepted a Russian proposal to relinquish control of its chemical arms stores:

BREAKING: Syrian foreign minister says Syria has accepted Russian proposal to surrender control over its chemical weapons. -- The Associated Press (@AP) September 10, 2013

On Monday, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moallem stated that his country welcomed the Russian proposal, which called for Syria to place its chemical weapons under international control and for the weapons to be destroyed.
